<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=372&amp;p=389#p389"><![CDATA[
Session 1<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9CTzhqVHmww&amp;t=86s">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9CTzhqVHmww&amp;t=86s</a><!-- m --><br />Q1. How do you like your beef to be cooked? Roast, Grill,Braise, Stew, or Saute?<br />Q2. Which cut of beef do you usually choose? <br />沙朗牛排(SIRLOIN)? 菲力 牛排（FILLET）? 丁骨牛排(T BONE)? 肋眼牛排(RIB EYE)?<br />牛小排( short ribs)? 紐約客牛排( New York strip steak )<br />Q3. How do you like your steak done?<br />     raw , blue-rare, rare,medium-rare,medium,medium-well,well-done?<br />Q4. Have you ever tried Wagyu steak ? What's the flavor?　Are there any differences　between Wagyu steak and other steaks?<br />---------------------------------------------<br />Session 2<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3uP2APeKh_M">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3uP2APeKh_M</a><!-- m --><br />Q 1. What are the ethical concerns about genome editing?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/health-46342195">https://www.bbc.com/news/health-46342195</a><!-- m --> China baby gene editing claim 'dubious'<br />Q 2. If you were a scientist , what disease would you want to modify genetically ? Why?<br />Q 3.Any benefit and after effects can this kind of baby gene editing bring ?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Mon Mar 16, 2020 12:27 am</p><hr />
